<p>Is it the same?
- It can be the same or not.
It is <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/CSS_preprocessor" rel="nofollow noreferrer">CSS preprocessor</a></p>

<p>First snippet is written as SCSS grammar.
So it is not normal CSS formatting, but you can say it is the same.
Because, if it is compiled, it will generate as the second snippet.</p>

<p>Here is an official link of style rules for SCSS
<a href="https://sass-lang.com/documentation/style-rules#nesting" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://sass-lang.com/documentation/style-rules#nesting</a></p>

<p>I think you better understand the basics of CSS first and then take a look at CSS preprocessor.</p>
